s' search for existential well-being on an increasingly interconnected planet. As a thorough exploration of daimistas' beliefs about the therapeutic potentials of ayahuasca, this book takes readers on an ethnographic journey into the deepest recesses of the human psyche.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Mrz 2024) 0aCultural pluralismxReligious aspects. 0aCultural pluralismzEurope. 0aReligion and culturezEurope. 0aSanto Daime (Cult)zEurope. 4aAnthropology and Archaeology : Anthropology of Religion. 4aPsychology : Psychology of Religion. 4aPsychology : Transpersonal Psychology. 4aReligion and Spirituality : New Religious Movements. 4aReligion and Spirituality : Religion. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Anthropology / Cultural & Social.2bisacsh40uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978143848315340uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781438483153423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781438483153/original  aGBV-deGruyter-alles